china comes up with an " important science and research plan " for future 15 years
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 9 ( reporter : li xing ) to promote china 's international competitive capacity , vigorously advance sustainable development , and realize a prioritized plan for surpassing ( developed countries ) , the " outline plan for the state 's medium - and long - term scientific and technological development ( 2006 to 2020 ) , " issued by the state council on the 9th , has arranged four important plans for scientific studies .
the four important scientific plans include protein studies , quantum adjustment and control studies , nano - studies , and growth and reproduction studies .
the outline points out that protein science is the peak of life science that developed countries are fiercely competing for .
in the next 15 years , china should focus on studying transcription repression histochemistry , protein histochemistry , metabolic histochemistry , structural biology , functions and interactions of protein biology , biology and systematic biology regarding protein calculation , methodology of protein studies and related application and basic studies , etc.
at the same time , the outline thinks that quantum adjustment and control studies has an obvious forward - looking nature , and might significantly impact the economic development of human society to an extent that can hardly be assessed in 20 to 30 years .
china should focus on studying the carrier , adjustment , and control rationales and methods of quantum communication , quantum calculation , the new quantum effect of constrained small quantum systems , quantum adjustment and control demonstration , and a new rationale and technical basis for quantum measurement , etc.
moreover , the outline points out that nano - technology has become the strategic selection for many countries to promote their core competitive capacity , and also is one of the fields for china to realize its surpassing development .
in the next 15 years , china will focus on studying in this field , including controllable equipment , self - assembly , and functionalization of nano - material , nano - electronics , nano - biology , nano - medicine , nano - size demonstration and metrology , and applications of nano - material and technology in fields such as energy , the environment , information , medicine , etc.
since china 's population is growing on a large scale , there are many birth defects , a serious shortage of organs for transplants , and the aging peak is coming , it urgently needs to make breakthroughs and technological innovations in the scientific theories on reproduction and development .
based on the outline , from 2006 to 2020 , china will focus on studying stem cell reproduction , differentiation , adjustment , and control ; production , maturity , and fertilization of reproductive cells ; the mechanism of declination and degenerative pathological changes in human reproductive functions ; and the safety and ethics of assisting reproduction of stem cells , and stem cell technology , etc.
the increase rate of housing prices fell nearly 7 % in shanghai last year
xinhua news agency , shanghai , february 9 ( reporter : huang tingjun ) . the state 's macro - adjustment and control policy on real estate achieved obvious effects in shanghai in 2005 .
as the newly issued data demonstrates , every real estate index in shanghai fell quite obviously , or its increase rate slowed down last year .
among them , the increase rate of commercial housing prices fell 6.6 percentage points compared with that of last year ; the increased value of real estate fell 4.1 % compared with that of last year .
pan jianxin , the head of the statistics bureau of shanghai city , introduced in a press conference a few days ago that the average sale price of commercial housing in all of shanghai city was 6,698 yuan per square meter in 2005 , and had increased 313 yuan compared with that in 2004 .
the sale price level of commercial housing for the whole year increased 9.2 % compared with that of last year , but the increase rate fell 6.6 percentage points compared with that of last year .
the increased value of real estate for the whole year was 67.23 billion yuan , and fell 4.1 % compared with that of last year .
the mortgage loan balance for individual housing in the loan balance of financial institutions was 264.494 billion yuan , and increased only 19.94 billion yuan during the year . but the increased loan balance was 72.809 billion yuan in 2004 .
pan jianxin said that the sale price for commercial housing was stable and fell when reviewing sale prices for real estate in shanghai during the entire year .
a statistical bulletin also demonstrates that , based on calculations from the newest data , in 2005 the increase rate of real estate prices in shanghai fell to some extent ; the average sale price of commercial housing was 6,698 yuan per square meter , and increased 313 yuan compared with the per square meter cost in 2004 .
the sale price level for housing in all of 2005 increased 9.7 % compared with that of last year , but the increase rate fell 6.2 percentage points compared with that of last year .
as he stated , all of shanghai city had invested 124.686 billion yuan for real estate development , and this increased 6.1 % compared with that of last year .
the area of housing sold was 31.5887 million square meters , and decreased 9.5 % .
the sale amount total for commercial housing during the entire year was 216.13 billion yuan , and decreased 4.5 % compared with that of last year .
two light aircrafts crashed in new zealand
xinhua news agency , wellington , february 9. two new zealand light planes crashed in the sky over the shannon area about 100 kilometers north of the capital , wellington , on february 9 , and two flight school students died in the planes .
as a person responsible for the local civil aviation department said , both of the pilots in the planes were students of the flight school at massey university , who were still in training and had not earned their flight licenses .
the two planes were flying in an uncontrolled airspace when the accident occurred . pilots who fly in this kind of airspace should be responsible for the navigation and safety conditions of their planes , according to regulations .
an eyewitness at the site where the accident occurred told new zealand media that he heard a big explosion when the planes crashed , and saw the planes falling quickly to the ground .
another eyewitness also confirmed that he heard a big explosion before the planes fell to the ground , and saw falling pieces of the planes .
the cause of the plane crash is currently unknown . the local civil aviation department will investigate it .
