china 's experts : " china 's military threat " touted by the united states is an unreasonable accusation .
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 9 ( reporters : li xuanliang , xiong zhengyan , lin liping ) . the quadrennial defense review formally submitted by the united states pentagon to the congress a few days ago first calls china " a newly arisen power that is most likely to challenge the united states militarily . "
experts think that this is an unreasonable accusation against china 's normal defense construction , and an interference in china 's internal affairs by exaggerating the " theory of china 's military threat . "
the quadrennial defense review is a new guidance document for national defense of the pentagon .
this 92 - page report uses three paragraphs to discuss the issue of china 's military strength and how the united states should cope with it . the report directly mentions the two terms of " china " and " chinese " 15 times , and says that , " as a major newly arisen power , china has the most military potential to compete with the united states ; if the united states does not take any countermeasures , china is very likely to develop destructive military technology , and break the us supremacy of traditional weapons . "
yao yunzhu , a research fellow at the world 's military study office of china 's military science academy , said that although senior us officials expressed similar views before , this is the first time for the united states to come up with the idea that " china is most likely to challenge the united states militarily as a newly arisen power " in a defense strategy report .
" this report first regards russia , india , and china as newly arisen strategic rivals , and especially , pays more attention to the so - called ' theory of china 's military threat , ' "
said major general peng guangqian , a research fellow at china 's military science academy .
the noticeable thing is that on the same day when the quadrennial defense review was submitted , us president bush also presented his administrative budget for the 2007 fiscal year to the congress , and the defense budget is as high as 439.3 billion dollars in the budget .
" if the budget for military activities in iraq and afghanistan is added , the defense budget for the us in the 2007 fiscal year will break the historical record of 500 billion dollars , " said peng guangqian . " and this almost amounts to the sum of military expenses of all the countries in the world . "
peng guangqian thinks that the us method of making " theories of threats from other countries " reflects its consistent style of " making enemies , " and its real goal is to strive for more defense funds and fish for more profits for the us 's gigantic defense industry groups .
experts said that compared with the large military expenses of the us , china 's military expenditure is quite limited .
deng hongzhou , a military expert who has participated in the writing of the china defense white paper many times , said that since the 90s of the 20th century , with the economic development , china 's defense funding has been increased to some extent , but it tends to fall in its ratio to the state 's financial expenditure in the same periods .
official data shows that comparing 2004 with 1979 , the ratio of china 's defense expenditure in the state 's financial expenditure was decreased nearly 10 percentage points .
china 's defense funding in 2005 was rmb 244.656 billion yuan , which only amounts to 1/14 of that of the us ; military expense per capita is only equal to 1/60 of that of the us ; and military expense per serviceman is about only 1/30 of that of the us armed forces .
" the us land area is about as big as china 's , but the gap in military expenditures between ( the two countries ) is so huge that there is no need to point out whose military strength indeed exceeds the needs of a justifiable defense , "
said peng guangqian .
teng jianqun , director of the study office at china 's armament control and disarmament association , said that the us side should objectively comment on china 's military construction , and china 's peaceful development does not mean that china and the united states will become military rivals in the future .
china 's defense white paper 2004 says that china firmly follows the path of peaceful development and implements a defensive policy of national defense .
china never threatened or threatens or will threaten any countries .
china has never established any military bases in any other countries so far , nor sent any troops to other countries ; but the united states has established more than a hundred overseas military bases , and deployed more than 100,000 troops in the asian region alone .
zhu feng , a professor at the international relations college of beijing university , said that both china and the united states should strengthen communications and exchanges through established channels between the two countries to promote understanding and mutual trust , thoroughly advance the constructive collaboration relation between china and the united states in the new century , and jointly develop and maintain peace and development in the world .
