japanese researchers have developed a new type of highly efficient manmade kidney
xinhua news agency , tokyo , february 13 ( reporter : qian zheng ) . researchers at japan 's tokai university have developed a type of manmade biological kidney that can not only function the same as a human kidney for catabolism , but can also keep useful substances in the body . since it is small in size and easy to transplant , it is hopeful that it will bring good news to patients who have kidney disease with the further development of the study .
as japan economic and industrial news reported a few days ago , the newly developed manmade biological kidney is composed of two parts . one is the " manmade nephron , " which filters metabolites and water in the blood ; the other is the " manmade urinary tubules , " which extract useful substances such as water and amino acids from the original urine and sends them back into the blood .
both the " manmade nephron " and " manmade urinary tubules " are made of hollow threads , and the internal walls of the " manmade urinary tubules " are paved with epithelial cells of urinary tubules that have the function of catabolism .
this type of epithelial cells can treat diseases caused by repeated hemodialysis and decompose the causative substance of " dialysis - related denatured starch " into an amino acid , and send it back into the blood . they can also send those substances necessary for the human body such as glucose , vitamins , and minerals back into the blood again .
previous manmade kidneys depended on the osmosis pressure gap of dialysis to filter metabolites , which cannot totally get rid of them , and does not have the function of making amino acids and other substances return into the blood .
researchers used goats to do the manmade kidney transplant experiment , and the inner walls of hollow threads of the manmade kidney are lined with epithelial cells from a hog .
two weeks later , researchers confirmed that the manmade kidney is able to function .
they are currently developing the manmade biological kidney using human kidney cells , and are about to do clinical studies after verification of its safety .
china 's secure power production still faces serious challenges
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 13 ( reporter : an pei ) . a leader of the state power supervision and control committee said on the 13th that although the secure power production generally maintained a stable status in 2005 , secure power production still faces serious challenges .
vice chairman of the state power supervision and control committee shi yubo said at the fifth ( expanded ) session of the national secure power production committee that in 2005 china 's secure power production was stable in general , and accomplished the task smoothly for power peak usage in the summertime , realized a secure power supply , actively coped with the strikes of natural disasters , and basically assured the secure and stable operation of power systems , greatly reduced equipment accidents in secure power production and general power network accidents , compared with those of last year , and the health level of power equipment was increased .
but he pointed out that with changes in power supply and demand situations , and that many of the newly established generating sets are put into operation one after another , secure power production will face new challenges .
these challenges include : regional , seasonal , and time interval power shortages still exist ; power supply and demand situations in some regions are still tense ; since a good mechanism for the price of power and coal has not been formed , supply of power and coal is still quite problematic ; at the same time , the falling power and coal quality problem has not been effectively controlled , and will seriously affect stable operations of generating sets ; some power network structures are fragile and their equipment is obsolete , which brings risks to systems ' safety ; frequent occurrences of accidents in power infrastructure construction have not completely changed , and the situation is still serious .
shi yubo said that with the further development of power system reform , many deep - rooted contradictions will be continuously exposed , and how to maintain stability of employee teams and assure a normal production order will be a new issue to face .
for the secure power production work in 2006 , shi yubo said that the basic control secure power production work should be further consolidated ; an emergency control mechanism for power safety should be established and quickly perfected to strengthen responsive capabilities for emergencies ; coordination between power factories and networks should be strengthened ; security of big dams should be assured ; safety control of power facility constructions should be strengthened to reduce occurrences of personnel injury and death accidents ; information delivery work should be continuously strengthened to assure the accurate , timely , and smooth flow of power safety information .
it has been learned that based on a new power safety control situation , this year the power supervision and control committee will revise and perfect the issued temporary regulations on accident investigation of power production , and at the same time will continuously issue and execute additional documents about the safety of the hydraulic power station dam and safety protection of the secondary power system this year .
in 2005 , the whole of chinese society used a total power of 2468.9 billion kwh , and increased 13.45 % compared with that of last year .
facing the situation in which power supply and demand is still tense , and the unfavorable status of transportation problems with coal , power , and oil , power enterprises have taken effective measures and strengthened equipment control , and prevented the occurrence of large equipment accidents in national power production in all of last year .
there were 74 power network accidents , which were reduced by 127 compared with those of last year ; equipment accidents were 427 , which were reduced by 132 compared with those of last year .
