successful heart transplant operation for infant conducted in shandong
xinhua news agency , jinan , february 17 ( zhang yuqing and shen yaoqin ) . the cardiovascular disease research institute of jinan military area command recently conducted a successful heart transplant operation on an infant .
the reporter could see in an intensive care room on the 17th that the infant - who experienced surgery 51 days after the operation - looked rosy in the face . data from every test and check showed normal , and the infant has passed the surgery risk period smoothly , and was excitedly playing with toys bought by medical workers .
as a doctor who was on duty that day explained , when the infant patient was sent to the hospital by his parents from a rural area of taian , shandong , his body looked blue , and he breathed with difficulty . after a check and diagnosis , he was found to have a cyanotic congenital heart disease and needed a heart transplant operation .
a heart transplant operation is the most difficult , risky , and complex of heart surgeries .
particularly , a heart transplant operation for an infant younger than 1 year old is uncharted territory at home at present .
the cardiovascular disease research institute of jinan military area command immediately organized experts that night , who did repeated demonstrations and carefully designed the surgery and after - operation care plan , created a new method for blood vessel connections , and conducted an animal experiment .
the operation formally began at 8 a.m. on december 28 , 2005 .
the supplied heart came from a dead infant who suffered a sudden stoppage of breath and palpitations because of lung aplasia congenitalis .
the operation required the connection of 6 blood vessels , and 510 stitches with needles . the distance between stitch points did not exceed 3 mm.
the operation lasted 295 minutes and was completely successful .
state safety supervision bureau : containment of frequently - occurring large and major accidents in coal mines is top of this year 's priorities
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 17 ( reporter : liu zheng ) . since four large mine accidents - in each of which around a hundred miners lost their lives - have continuously occurred , the serious situation of national safe production in the past year has caused " containment of frequently - occurring large and major accidents in coal mines " to become the highest among national safety supervision work priorities for this year .
the reporter learned from the state 's supervision and control bureau of safe production on the 17th that for the purpose of truly containing large and major accidents frequently occurring in coal or other mines , coal mines are the highest among priorities .
the state 's supervision and control bureau of safe production will focus on the following three things for coal mine safety this year :
-- continue to effectively fight for gas control .
" extraction first and collection later " should be the priority for gas control this year .
if a shaft that has dense gas does not practice the method of " extraction first and collection later , " it should be ordered by law to stop production immediately .
-- continue to effectively fight for consolidation and closure .
those 5,243 shafts announced to the public , and more than 700 coal mine shafts recently reported from many local areas , should be completely and truly shut down .
closure should be regarded as a regular activity , and those coal mines that damage resources , pollute the environment , and lack safe conditions , should be continuously shut down .
-- strengthen basic control of coal mine safety .
immediately correct and stop losing management in a few big state - owned mines , and guide small mines that have mismanagement in establishing standard safety and management systems .
especially , major state - owned coal mines should be paid more attention to , and any productions exceeding their capacities , intensities , and fixed number of employees should never be allowed .
the controlled percentages for safe production for this year require the number of deaths in various accidents nationwide to be decreased 3 % compared with that of last year , and among them , the number in coal mines to be decreased 3.5 % .
the number of large accidents that cause more than ten deaths each should be decreased by 5 % , and among them , the number in coal mines should be decreased 7 % .
these controlled percentages have been announced to every provincial people 's government , and local administrations are dividing them in terms of different levels and allocating them to grass - roots and businesses .
statistics show that there were 5,986 victims in coal mine accidents nationwide in 2005 , and the number was 0.7 % lower compared with that of last year .
however , large accidents that had more than ten victims each have increased , and the number of victims has increased 66.6 % compared with that of last year .
( international ) barroso appeals for every party to make compromise in negotiation for future status of kosovo
xinhua news agency , belgrade , february 17 ( reporter : he yi ) . news from pristina : chair of the european union committee barroso said in pristina , the capital of kosovo , on the 17th , that he hopes that all of the parties concerned are ready to make compromises in the negotiation process for the future status of kosovo , and to make efforts for the eventual establishment of a democratic and multi - ethnically integrated kosovo .
barroso also met the president of kosovo 's provisional authorities , sejdiu , and a representative of the ethnic serbs of kosovo , respectively , on that day and told the media that all of the parties concerned should have a tolerant attitude , and only a democratic and multi - ethnically integrated kosovo that respects government administration and protects the interests of minorities can be acknowledged by the international society .
he also stressed that the european union committee will try its best to help kosovo to develop .
barroso also is also concerned about the difficulties kosovo is now facing in the implementation of the eight requirements arrived at by the un on the democratic process in kosovo .
he thinks that implementation of these requirements is the critical element that will impact the unification between kosovo and europe .
he also appealed to all the serbs in kosovo to join in all of the organizations there and to make active contributions for the realization of a democratic and multi - ethnically integrated kosovo .
barroso arrived in the capital of kosovo , pristina , on that day for a one - day visit .
before that , barroso had visited croatia , serbia and montenegro . he will also visit macedonia , albania , bosnia and herzegovina .
( winter olympic games : stimulant ) news analysis : pyleva incident might be settled by leaving it unsettled
xinhua news agency , turin , february 17. news analysis : pyleva incident might be settled by leaving it unsettled
xinhua news agency reporters : gao peng , ding ying
although italy reiterated that any athletes who are discovered using stimulants may face the " disaster of being jailed , " many cases currently demonstrate that it is unlikely to happen to russian women 's biathlon athlete olga pyleva , who is at the center of the first scandal over stimulant use at the winter olympic games .
the first stimulant use scandal at the turin winter olympic games was exposed on the 16th , and olga pyleva was discovered to have used the illegal and banned drug carphedon .
the next day , the international olympic committee announced that pyleva had been thrown out of the winter olympic games , and the silver medal she won for the 15 km women 's biathlon had been withdrawn .
the same day , the international winter biathlon alliance determined to forbid pyleva to participate in the sport for two years .
the international olympic committee has been implementing the regulation that once athletes are discovered using stimulants , they will lose their qualification to participate in the games , and the scores they achieved will be withdrawn , but they are not subject to legal punishment .
however , according to italian law , the carrying and use of stimulants by any athlete are criminal activities . a law enforcement organization has the right to directly arrest and investigate any athlete who uses stimulants . any violators of the law are subject to jail for 3 months to 3 years .
the international olympic committee had been " bargaining " with the italian government for one year , and eventually reached an agreement last december . both sides agreed that during the period of the winter olympic games , any athletes who use stimulants would be handled according to italian laws .
through the unremitting efforts made by the international olympic committee , the italian side made a compromise four days before the opening ceremonies of the winter olympic games , and promised that the police would not enter the olympic village to search athlete residences during the olympic games . but any athletes whose drug tests show positive will be investigated by italian prosecution organizations .
some reports said that pescante , an official of the italian government responsible for supervision of the turin winter olympic games , has transferred pyleva 's stimulant case to a turin prosecution organization .
however , the international olympic committee and pescante himself have not confirmed this so far .
andrey dmytriev , a doctor for the russian biathlon team , disclosed at noontime on the 17th that pyleva had left turin and returned home .
shi kangcheng , a chinese sports official who had been in a position at the world anti - stimulant organization for many years , thinks that once pyleva returns home , this case might eventually " be settled by leaving it unsettled . "
shi kangcheng said that the international olympic committee and the italian government have not " completely addressed " the anti - stimulant issue at the winter olympic games , and it is hard to say what the outcome would be even if italian prosecution organizations really did get involved in the case .
based on past penalty cases in which italy sentenced or punished its own athletes who used stimulants , the most serious penalty was merely a " two - year probation . "
thus , senior reporter piali from the italian ansa said that the possibility of pyleva being jailed is " very small , " and at most , she might be fined .
piali also said that although an italian court could sentence her by default , it is impossible for the italian police to catch pyleva abroad and bring her back to serve the sentence .
if pyleva refuses to accept the sentence , the italian side can do nothing about it .
comprehensive news : new epidemic spots continuously emerge ; every country in the world taking strict prevention measures
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 18. a comprehensive report by xinhua news agency reporters abroad : bird flu is further spread on the african continent .
the world health organization confirmed on the 17th that birds have been found dead of infections by the bird flu virus in three areas of egypt .
in europe , france also first discovered the h 5 bird flu virus ; europe and africa are on high alert and strengthening prevention measures against the epidemic .
hussein bushila , a consultant for the eastern mediterranean region of the who , told press in egypt on the 17th that three areas in egypt - including cairo and jizah in the central region , and minya in the southern region - have found birds dead of h 5n1 bird flu virus infection ; egyptian government departments have started to kill poultries suspected of being infected with bird flu .
experts pointed out that egypt is an important passage for migrant birds in the middle east and north africa . the possibility of migrant birds bringing bird flu virus across borders is very high .
egypt has announced a ban on import of any live poultries from foreign countries , and strengthened quarantine work at border ports .
more than 800 chickens died of unknown causes on a chicken farm in the capital of cameroon , yaounde , in the past week .
cameroon has decided to immediately suspend imports of all poultries and pork from nigeria , where the bird flu epidemic was discovered , and discontinued trade of poultries and related products in markets in border areas between the two countries .
the cameroonian government has also established a monitoring and detection network that can cover its overall territories for epidemic detection . its bayside center and the state veterinary laboratory are also under an emergency status so that they can deploy any test work associated with the h 5n1 virus at any time .
in europe , denmark and sweden initially excluded the epidemic on the 17th .
the swedish veterinary institute issued a test result that shows the dead swans found in sweden this wednesday were not infected with the bird flu virus .
an initial test result done by the danish state veterinary control bureau also showed that the 30 dead swans found in danish territories in recent days were not infected with the bird flu virus .
but an agricultural department stated that denmark still cannot lower its guard .
9 bird flu epidemic spots have been discovered in romania in eastern europe this year . who experts in bucharest said on the 17th that bird flu has spread to almost every area of the delta region of the danube river , and the situation must be carefully coped with , and romania might be continuously threatened by bird flu within 3 to 5 years .
in bangladesh in asia , the government has taken every measure necessary to prevent bird flu .
the government 's poultry service bureau has provided related officials books about prevention of bird flu , and also simultaneously organized poultry raisers for trainings .
( newspaper digest ) china 's first blood sharing information management system established in zhejiang
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 18. as the blood center of zhejiang province disclosed , china 's first blood sharing information data management and control network system has recently been formally established at the center and has been put into operation .
a leader involved with the blood center of zhejiang province said that this means that any citizen who has freely donated his blood in any county ( city , district ) blood collection and supply institutions of zhejiang province will have a unique code record . when he donates blood again , information that determines if he is qualified to donate his blood will immediately show up as long as his code record , individual information , blood type , blood donation record , and time of last blood donation are entered .
the leader further explained that if the system shows a free - blood donor is still within an interval period through entering the related code records , it will point out that the person does not meet the requirements for blood donation at this time .
in this way it can protect not only the health of the blood donor , but also the health and safety of blood recipients .
in addition , when the blood supply is in shortage , a blood donor or his relatives can have the right to use his blood first . as long as you enter a valid i.d. for the blood donor , his related information will show up , which is pretty convenient .
as today 's morning journal of hangzhou reported , the information system has currently been put into operation in 36 blood collection and supply institutions throughout the province . and the blood resources status for all of the blood collection and supply institutions in the province can also be shown in real time , which has accomplished data sharing throughout the province .
11 villages hurriedly evacuated in case mudslide occurs again
xinhua news agency , manila , february 18. local philippines officials said on the 18th that 11 villages in the eastern philippines have been hurriedly evacuated in case a similar mudslide occurs again .
rosette lerias , a southern leyte province official , said on that day that those villages are located in the same area as the village where a mudslide occurred on the 17th , and the terrain features are similar .
residents of the 11 villages who were evacuated will be placed in 7 evacuation centers .
lerias said that the government ordered residents to evacuate yesterday , and today it sent people to check those villages because some of the villagers do not want to leave their homes .
the mudslide incident occurred on the 17th close to a village located beside a mountain in st. bernard township in the southern part of south leyte province . mud and rocks had buried the entire village , and only a few roofs could be seen from tv footage .
since mud is very thick and wet , there is almost no hope for buried humans to survive .
at present , 109 people have been found dead and 57 people have been rescued .
as has been estimated , the number of deaths caused by the incident may be as high as 1,800 .
( overseas chinese towns and their sentiments ) exports in first month of this year in quanzhou , overseas chinese town in south fujian , increased 35.2 % compared with that of last year
xinhua news agency , fuzhou , february 19 ( guo yu ) . foreign trade in quanzhou city continued to maintain its high - speed growth tendency in january of this year .
based on statistics from the customs office , exports for quanzhou in january reached 0.33 billion usd , which is the best score in history , and increased 35.2 % compared with that of last year , and is higher than the average growth level of the whole province .
as the foreign trade and economic bureau of quanzhou city estimated , the reason why the foreign trade for quanzhou grew rapidly in january is because it had benefited from several foreign trade support services and measures taken by quanzhou ; enterprises were very enthusiastic about promoting exports ; economic operations in quanzhou were thriving ; enterprises raised their confidence in running businesses ; and there was a highly efficient and unblocked environment for development of foreign trade .
